# AllVet App - Project Context

## What
Expense and income tracking app for veterinarians. Start simple, design for growth.

## Who
Solo developer with 5+ years in computer graphics/3D web, using this to level up in fullstack React, clean architecture, and product planning.

## Key Constraints
- Supabase (PostgreSQL, Auth) as backend. See `docs/decisions/001-backend-stack.md`
- Google Drive for all file storage (documents, receipts, backups) — Supabase holds references only
- PWA for mobile-friendly use
- TypeScript + React
- Clean Architecture: domain layer has zero external dependencies
- SOLID principles throughout
- Every architectural decision must be documented in `docs/decisions/` before or alongside implementation

## Learning Goals
- Clean architecture in practice
- React patterns (hooks, context, state management)
- Full product lifecycle (spec → design → build → ship)
- Data layer abstraction (repository pattern for backend swappability)

## Documentation
All specs, decisions, and learnings live in `docs/`. Always check `docs/` for context before starting work.

## Style
- Simple, concise communication
- Challenge requirements when something seems off
- Explain architectural "why" not just "what"
